Interest Calculator Code of Conduct

1. Purpose:
The Interest Calculator community is committed to providing a respectful and inclusive environment for all contributors. This Code of Conduct outlines our expectations for everyone involved in our project, both online and offline.

2. Our Standards:

    Be respectful and considerate of others.
    Refrain from any form of harassment, discrimination, or offensive behavior.
    Foster an open and welcoming community where diverse perspectives are valued.
    Show empathy towards fellow contributors, and be open to constructive criticism.

3. Unacceptable Behavior:
The following behaviors are considered unacceptable and will not be tolerated:

    Harassment, discrimination, or intimidation of any form.
    Offensive comments, jokes, or imagery.
    Any form of trolling, spamming, or unwelcome solicitation.
    Disruptive or disrespectful behavior during discussions.

4. Reporting Guidelines:
If you experience or witness any unacceptable behavior, please report it to the project maintainers at [maintainers@email.com]. All reports will be kept confidential.

5. Enforcement:
Violations of this Code of Conduct will result in appropriate and fair actions, including warnings, temporary bans, or permanent expulsion from the project as necessary.

6. Attribution:
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.1.
